00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:22,060
Okay.

125
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:24,440
The event is the snap of the cords.

126
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:27,800
The wave that follows is just the ringing of the flesh.

127
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:40,840
By focusing purely on the peaks, the system avoids getting bogged down in redundant, predictable data, and instead extracts a highly concentrated, physically interpretable sequence.

128
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:48,620
So you were saying the emotion, the intent, isn't in the shape of the whole wave, it's in the timing and the force of the snaps.

129
00:10:48,620 --> 00:10:49,060
Yes.

130
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:56,260
The paper argues that porosity is governed by statistical regularities that persist across different volumes and environments.

131
00:10:56,820 --> 00:10:57,700
These are invariants.

132
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:02,100
The measurement operator extracts an eight-dimensional vector from these peaks.

133
00:11:02,420 --> 00:11:03,220
Eight dimensions?

134
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:03,860
Yes.

135
00:11:04,340 --> 00:11:10,620
It is not an AI listening to the recording and guessing, oh, the speaker sounds sad.

136
00:11:10,620 --> 00:11:16,380
It is hard physics measuring the literal tension in your throat.

137
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:20,780
See, if I were trying to measure a voice, I'd probably just track volume and pitch.

138
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,700
Loud and high means angry.

139
00:11:23,020 --> 00:11:24,780
Quiet and low means calm.

